<Author>ceedaworld
<Content>Nice staff The hotel is easy to find. It is on a very busy street. There are rooms that face the back. Back rooms are smaller. Bath is huge and clean. Beds are comfortable. The staff is so nice. Very helpful and friendly from front desk to maids.The hotel like many in Barcelona exist above the metro. At quiet times, one can hear the trains roll under the hotel. This happens in better hotels too. A very good tapa bar is 100 meters from the the hotel: turn right toward the train stop it is right on the corner. A bit pricey, but very tasty. Tapas of all sort in the window. Look for this. Breakfast is very adequate. Hot and warm selections. The hotel is three stops from Catalunya. It is nice to be away from the La Ramlas maddness and come to the room. The hotel is not too bad and not the best, but adequate for the budget traveler. The NH hotel chain has many different levels and this fits the bill for a budget one. Enjoy! 
