<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Troubled times amplified During a very difficult time when my father required heart surgury we were placed in two different NH group hotels, the first being the Belagua where the staff were very sympathetic. Unfortunatley, as this group of hotels do not know their availability on a daily basis until late afternoon/early evening we had the misfortune to be moved to their sister hotel NH Condor where the staff lacked tremendously in customer care, one in particular was the tall slim male desk clerk. If you want to sleep and go its ok but if you want that little extra that makes your stay special this is not the hotel.  
